{
  "question_text": "<h3>Time Based Key-Value Store</h3><p>Design a time-based key-value data structure that can store multiple values for the same key at different time stamps and retrieve the key's value at a certain timestamp.</p>",
  "difficulty": "MEDIUM",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "Operations list.",
  "output_format": "Results list.",
  "constraints": [
    "10^5 total calls across set and get",
    "timestamps are strictly increasing"
  ],
  "explanation": "Use a hash map where keys map to a list of (timestamp, value) pairs. Since timestamps are added in increasing order, the lists remain sorted. Use binary search (bisect_right) to find the value for a given timestamp.",
  "answer": "class TimeMap:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.m = collections.defaultdict(list)\n    def set(self, key, value, timestamp):\n        self.m[key].append((timestamp, value))\n    def get(self, key, timestamp):\n        if key not in self.m: return \"\"\n        arr = self.m[key]\n        i = bisect.bisect_right(arr, (timestamp, chr(127)))\n        return arr[i-1][1] if i > 0 else \"\"",
  "boilerplate": {
    "python": "import sys\nimport json\n\ndef solve(*args):\n    # Implement 981 Time Based Key-Value Store here\n    pass\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    data = sys.stdin.read().strip().split('\\n')\n    if not data or data == ['']: sys.exit(0)\n    args = [json.loads(line) for line in data]\n    print(json.dumps(solve(*args)))",
    "cpp": "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <string>\n#include <algorithm>\nusing namespace std;\nint main() { string line; while (getline(cin, line)) {} return 0; }",
    "java": "import java.util.*;\nimport java.io.*;\npublic class Main {\n    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {\n        BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(System.in));\n        String line; while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {}\n    }\n}",
    "javascript": "const fs = require('fs');\nfunction solve(...args) { return 0; }\nconst lines = fs.readFileSync(0, 'utf8').trim().split('\\n');\nif (lines.length) { console.log(JSON.stringify(solve(...lines.map(l => JSON.parse(l))))); }\nmodule.exports = solve;",
    "c": "#include <stdio.h>\n#include <stdlib.h>\nint main() { return 0; }"
  },
